  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "Currently, we just run the prepare phase of the xtrabackup restore with the `--defaults-file`, `--prepare` and `--target-dir` flags.  We should allow passing of the `--use-memory` flag, with a parameter, to allow speeding up of the prepare phase.  Since the restore (and prepare phase) are typically run on the shard host, there is usually plenty of memory available to dedicate to speeding up this phase.\r\n\r\nDocumentation for the flag here:  https://www.percona.com/doc/percona-xtrabackup/2.4/xtrabackup_bin/xbk_option_reference.html#cmdoption-xtrabackup-use-memory",
